defaulte benefits 
defaultof 
defaultincreased deployment for
default GSHPs
default, the chart below shows the 2020 annual 
defaultresource costs rate per technology. Annual resource cost measures the annual net incremental costs of installing a renewable heating system instead of a conventional one. The costs take into account the annual operational benefits (if any) but exclude any 
defaultsubsidy
default, thereby identifying, in the absence of any market interventions, an underlying merit order of options available in meeting a particular policy objective
default. With sensible assumptions about price reductions
default from now to 2020
default, GSHPs are a valuable inves
defaulttment and provide a cheaper way of producing renewable energy than 
defaultsome 
defaultother technologies
default already supported by 
defaultG
defaultovernment through other schemes such as the Renewables Obligation
default. Ther
defaulte is therefore a strong case to increase the subsidies paid to GSHPs, ev
defaulten if initially that subsidy is higher than some other technologies used to meet the renewables target, in order to ensure their proper deployment as a cost effective means for the country overall in meeting the renewables target.
